des:
A weekly sports update featuring local sports happenings around the Fergus Falls, Minnesota area from youth to adult.

Daily Journal Media publishes a community-oriented newspaper that focuses on the people of Fergus Falls and the surrounding area. Its role is to chronicle the community it serves through unbiased reporting, informative advertising, and interesting features, photographs, and commentary. Where possible it seeks to accentuate the positives, but never ignores the negatives. Daily Journal Media has been part of the Fergus Falls community for 147 years. It was founded in 1873 by A. J. Underwood, whose family published the newspaper until the mid-1980’s when it was purchased by Thomson Newspapers. In December 1992 it was sold to Boone Newspapers Incorporated who operated it until July 2019 when it was purchased by Wick Communications, a family-owned community media company with newspapers, websites, magazines, and specialty publications in 10 states. The home office is in Sierra Vista, Arizona, and Wick publishes newspapers in Arizona, Alaska, Colorado, Idaho, Louisiana, Montana, North Dakota, Oregon, South Dakota, and Washington.
